					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">There are two different DMA paths in the NES: the $4014 blit-sprite-memory, which always starts reading from an address $xx00 and writes to $2004, and the DPCM which starts reading at $xyz0, x≥0xC, z={0,4,8,C} and goes for 16*w+1.
<br />
<br />Looking at the timing diagram, this looks like
<br />* read from 0, write to 4
<br />* read from 1, write to 4
<br />* read from 2, write to 4
<br />* read from 3, write to 4
<br />* read from 4, write to 4
<br />.. &amp;c. So it looks like this is the $4014 DMA.
<br />
<br />If you tie pin 30 on the 2A03 high (which the wiki states should disable the extra sound &amp;c hardware) does it stop happening?</div>

