						<div class="postbody"><div class="quotetitle">skrasms wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent">I would expect step 6 would issue a BRK command, so then I would see 0xE and 0xF come up next. Why does it instead turn to 0x1 followed by three write commands before 0xE and 0xF show up on the address bus?<br /></div>
<br />
<br />I suspect 0x1 is it fetching the 'operand' for the BRK instruction, and the writes to 0xD,0xC,0xB are it pushing the processor status and return address onto the stack.</div>

